            <p>ΘΑΡΣΙ<lb/>ΦΙΛΟΥ<lb/>ΕΤ<lb/>Ο
				</p>
         </div>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" subtype="transcription" xml:id="tala0003.transcription" corresp="#tala0003.diplomatic #tala0003.translation">
            <p>θάρσι <lb/> Φιλοῦ <lb/>
               <expan>
                  <abbr>ἐτ</abbr>
                  <ex>ῶν</ex>
               </expan>
               <lb/> ο'
				</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="tala0003.translation" corresp="#tala0003.diplomatic #tala0003.transcription">
            <p>Be of good courage, Philous! Seventy years old.
				</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Tombstone, inscription complete. Φιλοῦ may be read as the vocative for Φιλοῦς, which can be either masculine or feminine.</p>
         </div>
